<subSubSection id="C31990A8FFAFFF85FF01FBE38525FA7E" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFAFFF85FF01FBE38521FBE6" blockId="17.[168,775,1023,1716]" box="[168,639,1112,1132]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020">
<taxonomicName id="4C03B8A0FFAFFF85FF01FBE3850FFBE6" authority="Hackel (1911)" authorityName="Hackel" authorityYear="1911" box="[168,593,1112,1132]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="lanigera" variety="tandilensis">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAFFF85FF01FBE38646FBE6" box="[168,280,1112,1131]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020">Poa lanigera</emphasis>
Nees var. 
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAFFF85FEDBFBE28690FBE6" box="[370,462,1112,1131]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020">tandilensis</emphasis>
Hackel (1911)
</taxonomicName>
: 152.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFAFFF85FF67FBCC864BFB5C" blockId="17.[168,775,1023,1716]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020">
Cryptophytes, endemic to mountain ranges of 
<collectingRegion id="49C70DC1FFAFFF85FD1EFBCD8614FB3D" country="Argentina" name="Buenos Aires" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020">Buenos Aires province</collectingRegion>
. Vulnerable for reasons unknown (
<bibRefCitation id="EF92BED2FFAFFF85FD14FB228657FB5C" author="Delucchi G" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020" pagination="19 - 31" refId="ref30263" refString="Delucchi G (2006) Las especies vegetales amenazadas de la Provincia de Buenos Aires: una actualizacion. Aprona Boletin Cientifico 39: 19 - 31." type="journal article" year="2006">Delucchi 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFAFFF85FF67FB638525FA7E" blockId="17.[168,775,1023,1716]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAFFF85FF67FB6386DCFB7C" bold="true" box="[206,386,1241,1265]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020">Characteristics.</emphasis>
Dioecious, perennial, caespitose species, to 
<quantity id="4CFB6EC6FFAFFF85FEB2FB40861CFA9C" box="[283,322,1274,1298]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
tall, with erect, 1- or 2-node culms. Leaves parallel-veined, conduplicate, coriaceous, glaucous to glaucous-green, with rough margins and midribs. Basal innovations flabellate, leaf-sheaths compressed. Leaves plane, with a hooded apex, to 
<quantity id="4CFB6EC6FFAFFF85FE5FFAC08565FA1F" box="[502,571,1402,1426]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020" unit="cm" value="50.0">50 cm</quantity>
long; ligule membranous. Inflorescence: a compact panicle, to 
<quantity id="4CFB6EC6FFAFFF85FD20FA218595FA3F" box="[649,715,1435,1459]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020" unit="cm" value="20.0">20 cm</quantity>
long; female and male florets similar, multiflorous, pubescent, 
<quantity id="4CFB6EC6FFAFFF85FF01FA61864AFA7E" box="[168,276,1499,1523]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020" unit="mm" value="4.75" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5–6 mm</quantity>
long. Fruit: a fusiform caryopsis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31990A8FFAFFF85FF67FA418621F96B" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFAFFF85FF67FA418562F939" blockId="17.[168,775,1023,1716]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAFFF85FF67FA41860EF99E" bold="true" box="[206,336,1531,1555]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020">Comments.</emphasis>
This is an infrequent species in the study area. It grows in shallow soils and in rock cracks on slopes and summits. It can be differentiated from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C03B8A0FFAFFF85FF01F9E78679F9F9" box="[168,295,1628,1652]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAFFF85FF01F9E7878DF9F9" box="[168,211,1629,1652]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020">Poa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
of the area by its caespitose, glaucouse foliage and by its conduplicate leaves with flabellate basal innovations, as in several 
<taxonomicName id="4C03B8A0FFAFFF85FE15F9278562F939" box="[444,572,1692,1716]" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Iris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAFFF85FE15F92786BFF939" box="[444,481,1693,1716]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020">Iris</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFAFFF85FF01F9748621F96B" blockId="17.[168,383,1742,1766]" box="[168,383,1742,1766]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020">
Superorder 
<taxonomicName id="4C03B8A0FFAFFF85FE8CF9758621F96B" authorityName="Takhtajan" authorityYear="1967" box="[293,383,1743,1766]" class="Magnoliopsida" kingdom="Plantae" pageId="17" pageNumber="1020" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="superOrder" superOrder="Rosanae">Rosanae</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
